Title: Object: St Mary Egyptiaca
Description: St Maria Egyptiaca, praying with her right breast exposed and her hands crossed in front of her body; after Domenichino (?). c.1700 colour mezzotint, printed from four plates.
Producer name: Print made by: Jakob Christoph Le Blon
Curator's comments: This impression is trimmed; the plates for yellow and blue ink unfinished. The shades in the blue robe coloured by hand with black washes with white dots. For another impression, see 1846,0425.4. For more information on this print, see: Rodari (ed): 'Anatomie de la couleur; I'invention de l'estampe en couleurs', cat 48
